# Backend API base URL
VITE_API_URL=https://api.inzighted.com/api

# PDF service URL (for report generation)
VITE_PDF_SERVICE_URL=https://pdf.inzighted.com/pdf

# ============================================================================
# Multi-Tenant Subdomain Redirect (Production Only)
# ============================================================================
# The frontend automatically redirects users from web.inzighted.com to their
# institute's subdomain (e.g., rgracademy.inzighted.com) after successful login.
#
# ENVIRONMENT DETECTION (Dual-Signal):
# Redirect triggers ONLY when BOTH conditions are true:
#   1. Frontend hostname === "web.inzighted.com"
#   2. VITE_API_URL === "https://api.inzighted.com/api" (production API)
#
# This ensures:
#   ✅ Dev (tamilnadu.inzighted.com + tamilnaduapi) NEVER redirects
#   ✅ Prod (web.inzighted.com + api) DOES redirect
#   ✅ Cannot rely on import.meta.env.MODE (always "production" for all builds)
#
# BACKEND REQUIREMENT:
# All login endpoints (/admin/login/, /educator/login/, /institution/login/, 
# /student/login/) must include the following field in their response:
#
#   {
#     "token": "...",
#     "institute_subdomain": "rgracademy"  // <-- Add this field
#     // ... other fields
#   }
#
# BEHAVIOR:
# - If institute_subdomain is missing/null, no redirect happens (safe fallback)
# - Tokens are persisted in localStorage before redirect
# - Full URL context preserved (pathname, query params, hash)
# - Infinite loops prevented by hostname check
# ============================================================================